<main id="content" class="content"> <h1 class="title">My Emacs Elevator Pitch
 <br></br> <span class="subtitle">Aug 10, 2025 17:07</span>
</h1>
 <p>
This is my post for this month’s  <a href="https://www.emacswiki.org/emacs/Carnival">Emacs Carnival</a>, “Your Elevator Pitch for Emacs.” 
</p>

 <p>
It’s very simple. There is one thing that I have  <i>never</i> heard an Emacs user say:
</p>

 <blockquote>
 <p>
I’m forced to use Emacs for this particular task, but I sure wish I could use something else.
</p>
</blockquote>

 <p>
Why would you not want to at least  <i>try</i> something that its users love that much?
</p>


